Pre-Game Insights: Group D of the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers will see Benin and Libya square off at the Stade Felix Houphouet-Boigny on Tuesday.
Both teams will be aiming to win their first game of the qualifiers.
Benin lost 3-0 to Nigeria in their previous match, aiming to restart their quest for a spot in Morocco after finishing in the quarterfinals in 2019.
Libya last participated in the continental championship back in 2012, when they were eliminated in the group stages.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be held at the Stade Felix Houphouet-Boigny.
